-- в”Җв”Җ GOD MODE в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ
-- Only resets health locally. Does NOT block remotes.
-- Real god mode in most games requires server-side work,
-- but health loop + Attribute hook covers client-authoritative games.
local function startGodMode()
    State.godConn = RunService.Heartbeat:Connect(function()
        safePcall(function()
            local hum = getLpHum()
            if hum and hum.Health > 0 and hum.Health < hum.MaxHealth then
                hum.Health = hum.MaxHealth
            end
        end)
    end)

    -- hook Util.Attribute.Set to intercept health writes on our character
    if UtilAttribute then
        hookModFn(UtilAttribute, "Set", function(instance, key, value, ...)
            local orig = State.hookedFunctions["Set"]
            local chr  = LP.Character
            if chr and instance == chr then
                local kl = tostring(key):lower()
                if kl == "health" or kl == "currenthealth" then
                    return orig(instance, key, chr:FindFirstChildOfClass("Humanoid") and
                        chr:FindFirstChildOfClass("Humanoid").MaxHealth or value, ...)
                end
            end
            return orig(instance, key, value, ...)
        end)
    end
end

local function stopGodMode()
    if State.godConn then State.godConn:Disconnect() State.godConn = nil end
    -- restore hookfunction if we hooked Set
    if State.hookedFunctions["Set"] and UtilAttribute then
        safePcall(function()
            hookfunction(UtilAttribute.Set, State.hookedFunctions["Set"])
            State.hookedFunctions["Set"] = nil
        end)
    end
end

-- в”Җв”Җ SPEED HACK в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ
local function startSpeedHack()
    State.speedConn = RunService.Heartbeat:Connect(function()
        safePcall(function()
            local hum = getLpHum()
            if hum then
                local target = 16 * State.SpeedMultiplier
                hum.WalkSpeed = target
                -- rawset into UtilCharacter if it caches base speed
                if UtilCharacter then
                    rawset(UtilCharacter, "WalkSpeed", target)
                    rawset(UtilCharacter, "BaseSpeed",  target)
                    rawset(UtilCharacter, "MoveSpeed",  target)
                end
            end
        end)
    end)
end

local function stopSpeedHack()
    if State.speedConn then State.speedConn:Disconnect() State.speedConn = nil end
    safePcall(function()
        local hum = getLpHum()
        if hum then hum.WalkSpeed = 16 end
        if UtilCharacter then
            rawset(UtilCharacter, "WalkSpeed", 16)
            rawset(UtilCharacter, "BaseSpeed",  16)
            rawset(UtilCharacter, "MoveSpeed",  16)
        end
    end)
end

